<title>DENMARK: Protest stoppages hit Tele Danmark.</title>
<headline>Protest stoppages hit Tele Danmark.</headline>
<dateline>COPENHAGEN 1997-01-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>Danish telecoms group Tele Danmark said on Thursday that thousands of employees were involved in protest action against drastic staff cuts announced on Wednesday as part of a major streamlining programme.</p>
<p>&quot;Several thousand staff are involved in protest meetings, talks with management or direct strike action in protest against the programme,&quot; a Tele Danmark spokeswoman told Reuters.</p>
<p>&quot;The situation is rather confused, many staff have gone home, some are staging stoppages. I cannot say at this moment if we are talking about 2,000 or 10,000 staff,&quot; she added</p>
</text>
